ce:section.ce:para:
The sensitivity of S-N-CDs to Fe3+ ions was thoroughly analyzed using a solution containing Fe3+ at different concentrations (0–600 µM). The S-N-CDs fluorescence spectra are displayed in Fig. 10
                        a. Fluorescence intensity decreased as Fe3+ ion concentration increased. S-N-CDs exhibited robust fluorescence intensity when λex = 320 nm and λem = 410 nm. However, the fluorescence intensity dropped to 62 % with the addition of 600 µM Fe3+ ions. These findings unequivocally demonstrated the high sensitivity of S-N-CDs toward Fe3+ ions. Importantly, these results were consistent with previous studies [16,56], confirming the consistency of the findings and S-N-CDs sensitivity to Fe3+ ions. Plotting the quenching ratio (F0 − F)/F0 against Fe3+ concentration in the 0–600 µM range gave a linear regression curve (Fig. 10b). A high correlation coefficient (R2) of 0.9973 was obtained by a linear regression equation. Using the 3.SD/B and 10.SD/B equations (where the response curve's standard deviation is represented by SD and the calibration curve's slope is represented by B), the detection limit (LOD) and the quantitation limit (LOQ) of S-N-CDs for Fe3+ ions were found to be 33.19 and 110.64 µM, respectively. Compared to previous studies (Table 2
                        ), S-N-CDs synthesized from plastic bags as Fe3+ sensors exhibited a broad linear detection range of 110.64–600 µM.
